	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />0.02 is out. It has a greatly expanded manual and two new test screens.<br /><br />Turns out it takes about 8 ms for the sampling process to complete. So don't try reading it faster than twice per frame, and don't read it twice in a row the way you would to detect DMC bit deletions on a standard controller. However, you can calculate the current acceleration by taking the difference between the value at time t-1 and the average of the values at times t and t-2. If its absolute value exceeds about 10, something glitchy happened.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
